readability_reflection: I enjoyed concatenation more because it was easier to think of adding strings together than looking at the brackets to understand how to add strings together.
comprehension_debugging: String concatenation was easier for me to look at and understand adding strings together. It was personally harder for me to differentiate between brackets and parentheses for string interpolation.
preference_rationale: I would choose string concatenation because it's easier to look at.
learning_curve: My prior familiarity impacted my ease of understanding how concatenation works. I have seen and used concatenation in my computer science assignments for quite some time, and have never seen interpolation before. Because of this, I understood and could read concatenation much easier than interpolation.
